b'Several Indian airlines collapsed sadly including KFA. Now the previously unthinkable has happened with the collapse of Jet. Genuine business failures. But I am criminally charged by CBI/ED despite offering 100% payback. Wonder why only me ?'

b'Watched TV debate on the sad collapse of Jet which included unpaid employees and Industry veterans. Important issues on unemployment and suffering, security available to Banks, prospects of revival etc. Here I am offering 100 % payback of KFA loans which Banks wont take. Why ?'

b'SBI Lawyers in U.K. making presentations on their accomplishments against me. Indian Tax payers cost. Despite full recovery in India confirmed by the Prime Minister himself. https://t.co/K4HnvQhvq8'
b'SBI UK Lawyers in self promotion at Indian public cost. SBI must answer. https://t.co/QlmqKUJHW8'

b'To substantiate my point, assets belonging to me in the U.K. were sold and the costs of sale were almost 50 percent of value. The remaining assets yet to be sold won\xe2\x80\x99t cover legal costs. So what\xe2\x80\x99s this all about ? To enrich UK Lawyers? SBI please answer.'

b'Whilst media love sensational headlines, why doesn\xe2\x80\x99t anybody ask the PSU State Bank of India under RTI on how much they are spending on legal fees trying to recover money from me in the UK when I have offered 100 percent payback in India.'

b'None other than the Prime Minister of India specifically says in an interview that his Government has recovered more money than I allegedly owe PSU Banks and the same Banks claim otherwise in English Courts. Who does one believe ? One or the other is lying.'

b'Even though we were fierce competitors, my sympathies go out to Naresh and Neeta Goyal who built Jet Airways that India should be extremely proud of. Fine Airline providing vital connectivity and class service. Sad that so many Airlines have bitten the dust in India. Why ?'

b'Every time I say that I am willing to pay 100 percent back to the PSU Banks, media say I am spooked, terrified etc of extradition from the U.K. to India. I am willing to pay either way whether I am in London or in an Indian Jail. Why don\xe2\x80\x99t Banks take the money I offered first ?'

b'I invested hugely into Kingfisher which rapidly grew to become India\xe2\x80\x99s largest and most awarded airline. True, Kingfisher borrowed from PSU Banks as well. I have offered to pay back 100 percent but am being criminally charged instead. Airline Karma ?'

b'Even though Jet was a major competitor to Kingfisher at the time I feel sorry to see such a large private airline on the brink of failure when Government used 35K crores of public funds to bail out Air India. Just being a PSU is no excuse for discrimination.'

b'I am asked for comment on being labelled a Fugitive Economic Offender. When I have placed assets on the table before the Hon\xe2\x80\x99Ble Karnataka High Court in excess of the PSU Bank claims how can I be an Economic Offender ? The Fugitive part falls away.'

b'It is sad that the narrative seems to question my honest intentions. There are no delaying tactics or any agenda to gain brownie points. What needs to be appreciated is a bona fide offer and commitment placed before the Hon\xe2\x80\x99Ble Karnataka HC. Let Justice play its part.'

b'I made my media statement concurrent with my settlement offer now and was unable to make such an offer before due to various circumstantial changes about the value of my assets available. However I have honestly pursued settlement efforts since 2016.'

b'It is incorrect that my settlement offer before the Hon\xe2\x80\x99Ble Karnataka HC was motivated by the latest charge sheet under the media reported Fugitive Ordinance. I always had honest intentions to settle and there is ample proof. Anyway I hope the sale of assets is approved for Banks'

b'Government wants to recover money loaned by PSU Banks. They used CBI and ED to attach and recover. I, myself have placed all assets before the Hon\xe2\x80\x99Ble Karnataka HC and submitted for sale. Banks should be very happy. But if the same CBI and ED object what do I do ?'

b'Government, Courts and Banks are rightfully concerned about Public money loaned by Public Sector Banks. I have made an application to the Hon\xe2\x80\x99Ble Karnataka HC showing assets far in excess of the Banks claims and requesting sale under judicial supervision. What more ?'

b'CBI and ED charge sheets specifically allege criminality with no intention to repay Banks. Since 2016 I have been making efforts to settle. Now I have placed everything before the Hon\xe2\x80\x99Ble Karnataka HC so where is the malafide ? Are Banks interested in repayment ?'
